description: Indicates the purpose of the account. Typically, expense accounts are used to purchase goods and services, while revenue accounts are used to receive funds from taxes and fees.
Describes the general classification of an account as a subset of expenses or revenues
Describes a subset of an account class, typically defined by a general function, service, or category of items
Describes the smallest subset of an account group, typically defined by a specific function, service, or item
Uniquely identifies an expense or revenue account. Revenue accounts begin with a 4 while expense accounts begin with a 5.
